CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 1, 1955, pg. 12, reads: "Car Winner - Ephraim Crockett of 617 Perry Street, was first prize winner at the Pittsburgh Pirates 'Prize Night' Sunday and won a brand new green, hard top, Plymouth coupe.  Seated in the new car is Crockett's wife."
TitMainTitle: Man handing car keys to prizewinner Ephraim Crockett and Mrs. Crockett for Plymouth coupe, at Forbes Field Auto Dealership
